OL,6,FThunderstorms are set to hit parts of
OL,7,Fthe UK on Sunday amid a record-
OL,8,Fbreaking September heatwave.
OL,10,FThe UK has now sweltered through six
OL,11,Fdays of temperatures above 30C in
OL,12,FSeptember for the first time.
OL,14,FWhile Saturday was named the hottest
OL,15,Fday of the year so far, with 32.7C
OL,16,Frecorded in Heathrow.
OL,18,FForecasters predict that Sunday could
OL,19,Fbe the seventh day in a row that
OL,20,Ftemperatures reach above 30C.
OL,3,CThunderstorm warning looms amid
OL,4,Crecord-breaking September heatwave
